FBIS4-33093 "drlat106_b_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 Antigua Haiti Central Bank Freezes Malval Government Funds Central Bank Freezes Malval Government Funds FL0106173394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1500 GMT 1 Jun 94 FL0106173394 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole French BFN [Text] The central bank, the Bank of the Republic of Haiti, has frozen nearly 15 million Haitian dollars belonging to the resigning government of Mr. Robert Malval. The funds, which have been blocked since the arrival on the scene of the provisional government of attorney Jonassaint, are for social and humanitarian programs. It should be noted that this money was provided by the U.S. Agency for International Development [USAID] and was aimed at financing USAID humanitarian projects and food and work programs for the impoverished.
